Japan to Begin Nuclear Compensation in October-January

-- B y   Y u j i   O k a d a
-- 
2011-05-17T11:53:15Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-17/japan-to-begin-nuclear-compensation-in-october-january-correct-.html
(Corrects timing of payments in headline, first
paragraph.)  Japan ’s government plans to start
making compensation payments to those affected by the Fukushima
nuclear disaster between October and January, a statement said.
Guidelines on interim payments will be issued by July, the
country’s nuclear disaster taskforce said in a statement today.  The government will build 15,200 temporary housing units by
early August for those forced to evacuate areas around the
Fukushima Dai-Ichi nuclear station, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Yuji Okada in Tokyo at 
